name: Andrew J. Lanza
bio: UF graduate. St. Pete native. Always learning...

name: Benjamin Jehl
bio: A native of northern Indiana, Ben moved to St. Pete two years ago while working in finance. Excited about designing and building technologies that shape the future, he wanted to follow his passion for the tech industry and decided to attend the SDG Academy. When Ben isn't coding, he enjoys playing guitar, sports, cooking, traveling and continually learning valuable skills.

name: Gabe Oleinik
tagline: Friendly face, looking for a friendly place
bio: I am a full stack web developer currently going through the Academy at Suncoast Developers Guild. Learning is one of my favorite things to do, so I find myself perpetually driven to learn the newest and most effective technologies to get the job done. I have many personal interests that fit neatly within the tech space, including but not limited to, development, cyber/information security, DevOps methodolgies, and more. There is always more to learn, and there is little that I find more exciting than that.

name: Justin Oliver Lee
tagline: Nice Looking and Responsive, my Websites of Course.
bio: Justin comes from a hospitality management background, and was looking for a career change. With a drive to learn, create, and build; web development was a perfect fit for him to fulfill these passions. Equipped with the knowledge gained from Suncoast Developers Guild, he is ready to solve the problems and face the challenges a career as Web Developer will present.

name: Karsten Rogers
tagline: Can't fail if you don't try

name: Matthew Cooke
bio: Matt has spent a majority of his life in the Tampa Bay area and is a USF graduate. He came to the SDG with never having written a line of code and has fully embraced the process. Passionate about his family, friends, and his dog Arwen. His hobbies include: playing board games, learning to be a better developer, rock climbing, and video games.

name: Michael Yenny
tagline: Pain is temporary, Pride is forever.
bio: I am a Full Stack Web Developer that is graduating from SDG. I'm excited for the opportunity to apply the skills I have learned at SDG with my strong communication, and customer relationship skills to the tech industry. When I'm not coding I enjoy spending time with my family and taking spontaneous adventures to cool places.
